      "content": "Sudafed (pseudoephedrine) is generally considered safe for use during the second trimester when taken sparingly, though you should still confirm with a pharmacist or your doctor before starting any new medication. Ciprofloxacin is a strong antibiotic that is typically prescribed for bacterial infections, but it is not usually recommended as a \"one-time\" remedy; instead, it is often used for a full course of treatment, so you must follow your doctor's instructions strictly. Since your clinic is closed, please call your OB-GYN office or a local pharmacist immediately to get a specific recommendation and prescription if needed, as self-treating with antibiotics can be risky.",
      "source": "target",
